export const SKILL_MARKDOWN = "---\nname: nehroai-admin\ndescription: >\n  Use this skill when creating, updating, listing, or exporting price quotes\n  (ОћОдОбОЋОф ОъОЌОЎОе) for Nehorai Hadad's portfolio admin, managing the brand profile,\n  or when the user says \"build a quote\", \"create a quote\", \"ОфОЉОаОћ ОћОдОбОф ОъОЌОЎОе\",\n  \"generate a quote PDF\", \"add a client quote\", \"send a price proposal\", or\n  anything involving the nehroai admin MCP tools or the /api/admin/v1 HTTP API.\n  Also use when the user asks about agent tokens, connecting an MCP to the admin,\n  or checking/updating the brand profile. Trigger even if the user does not\n  explicitly name MCP or API Рђћ any quote/PDF/brand task in this portfolio admin\n  warrants this skill.\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThe nehroai portfolio admin is a private owner-scoped service for managing\n**price quotes** and a **brand profile**. Quotes carry client details, line\nitems with quantity/unit-price/discount/VAT, auto-computed totals, and export\nas a branded A4 PDF. The system is bilingual (Hebrew `he` / English `en`);\nHebrew quotes render RTL.\n\nThere are two interfaces over the same service layer Рђћ pick the one that fits\nthe context.\n\n---\n\n## Choosing the interface\n\n| Situation | Use |\n|-----------|-----|\n| You are a Claude Code / Claude agent with MCP configured | **MCP** (preferred) |\n| You are an OpenAI-function-calling agent, a script, or have no MCP | **HTTP API** |\n| You need the OpenAPI contract to register tools automatically | `GET <origin>/api/admin/v1/openapi.json` (no auth required) |\n\n---\n\n## Authentication & connecting\n\n### Minting a token\n\nTokens look like `nh_...`, are owner-scoped, shown once, and revocable.\n\n- **Admin UI**: Settings Рєњ Agent tokens Рєњ Create\n- **CLI**: `pnpm token:create <owner-email> [label]`\n\nAll requests/tools resolve the owner from the token Рђћ never pass an owner or\nemail as a parameter.\n\n### Connecting via MCP (Claude Code)\n\n```bash\nclaude mcp add --transport http nehroai-admin \\\n  <origin>/api/admin/mcp/mcp \\\n  --header \"Authorization: Bearer <token>\"\n```\n\n`<origin>` is the dev or prod URL (e.g. `http://localhost:3000` or\n`https://nehoraihadad.com`).\n\n### HTTP API base\n\nAll endpoints sit under `<origin>/api/admin/v1` and require:\n\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer <token>\n```\n\n---\n\n## Installing / updating this skill\n\nAny Claude Code agent can self-install (or update) this skill with a single\ncommand Рђћ no manual copy-paste needed:\n\n```bash\nmkdir -p ~/.claude/skills/nehroai-admin\ncurl -fsSL https://ai.nehoraihadad.com/api/admin/v1/skill -o ~/.claude/skills/nehroai-admin/SKILL.md\n```\n\nThe next Claude Code session auto-loads skills from `~/.claude/skills/`, so\nthe skill is active immediately after restarting.\n\nNon-Claude agents (OpenAI function-calling, scripts, etc.) can fetch the same\nURL and inject the Markdown as system-prompt context. Add `?format=json` to\nget a structured envelope `{ name, description, markdown }` instead of raw\nMarkdown.\n\nThe production origin is `https://ai.nehoraihadad.com`. No authentication is\nrequired to fetch the skill Рђћ the content is documentation, not a secret.\n\n---\n\n## Capabilities\n\n### MCP tools\n\n| Tool | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `list_quotes` | List quotes; `format: \"concise\"` or `\"detailed\"` |\n| `create_quote` | Create a new quote (number allocated automatically) |\n| `get_quote` | Fetch one quote by id |\n| `update_quote` | Patch quote fields or items |\n| `delete_quote` | Delete a quote |\n| `get_brand` | Fetch brand profile |\n| `update_brand` | Update brand profile |\n| `get_quote_pdf` | Returns a base64 `application/pdf` resource |\n\n### HTTP API routes\n\n| Method | Path | Notes |\n|--------|------|-------|\n| `GET` | `/quotes?format=concise\\|detailed` | |\n| `POST` | `/quotes` | Create |\n| `GET` | `/quotes/{id}` | |\n| `PATCH` | `/quotes/{id}` | |\n| `DELETE` | `/quotes/{id}` | |\n| `GET` | `/quotes/{id}/pdf` | Returns binary PDF |\n| `GET` | `/brand?language=he\\|en` | |\n| `PUT` | `/brand` | |\n| `GET` | `/openapi.json` | Public OpenAPI 3.1 contract Рђћ no auth |\n\n---\n\n## Conventions (follow these precisely)\n\n- **Quote number** (`NH-YYYY-NNNN`) is allocated automatically on create.\n  Never invent or pass a number when calling `create_quote` / `POST /quotes`.\n- **Currency**: ILS (Рѓф). VAT defaults to **18%** (Israel standard).\n- **Language**: `\"he\"` or `\"en\"`. Hebrew quotes render right-to-left; brand\n  labels localize to match.\n- **Status lifecycle**: `draft` Рєњ `sent` Рєњ `approved | rejected | expired`.\n  New quotes default to `draft`.\n- **`validUntil`**: ISO date `YYYY-MM-DD`.\n- **Line item shape**:\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"description\": \"string\",\n    \"quantity\": 1,\n    \"unitPrice\": 0,\n    \"discountPct\": 0,\n    \"vatApplies\": true\n  }\n  ```\n  Item ids are assigned automatically; `discountPct` is 0РђЊ100.\n\n---\n\n## Workflow: build a quote and deliver the PDF\n\n### Step 1 Рђћ create the quote\n\nMCP:\n```\ncreate_quote {\n  \"language\": \"he\",\n  \"client\": { \"name\": \"Acme ОЉОб\\\"Оъ\", \"email\": \"x@acme.com\" },\n  \"projectTitle\": \"ОцОЎОфОЋОЌ ОљОфОе\",\n  \"items\": [\n    { \"description\": \"ОцОЎОфОЋОЌ\", \"quantity\": 10, \"unitPrice\": 500, \"vatApplies\": true },\n    { \"description\": \"ОбОЎОдОЋОЉ\", \"quantity\": 5,  \"unitPrice\": 300, \"vatApplies\": true }\n  ],\n  \"terms\": \"50% ОъОДОЊОъОћ\",\n  \"validUntil\": \"2026-09-30\"\n}\n```\n\nHTTP equivalent:\n```http\nPOST /api/admin/v1/quotes\nAuthorization: Bearer nh_...\nContent-Type: application/json\n\n{ ...same body... }\n```\n\nThe response includes the allocated `number` (e.g. `NH-2026-0003`), the `id`,\nand computed subtotal/VAT/total.\n\n### Step 2 Рђћ retrieve the PDF\n\nMCP:\n```\nget_quote_pdf { \"id\": \"<id from step 1>\" }\n```\nReturns a base64 `application/pdf` resource. Filename: `<number>.pdf`.\n\nHTTP:\n```http\nGET /api/admin/v1/quotes/{id}/pdf\nAuthorization: Bearer nh_...\n```\nReturns binary `application/pdf`.\n\n---\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n| Symptom | Likely cause |\n|---------|--------------|\n| `401 Unauthorized` | Token missing, wrong, or revoked. Re-check the `Authorization` header or re-mint a token in Settings. |\n| PDF endpoint returns 500 | PDF generation requires the Next.js server running (dev or prod). It uses `@sparticuz/chromium-min` Рђћ not available in edge/serverless cold starts without the runtime pack. |\n| Hebrew text displays LTR | The quote or template is using `language: \"en\"`. Set `language: \"he\"` on create or update. |\n| `create_quote` fails with \"number conflict\" | You passed a `number` field Рђћ remove it and let the server allocate. |\n| MCP tools not found | MCP not connected. Run the `claude mcp add` command above and verify the origin URL and token. |\n";
